23/04/2004
OPATIJA, Croatia -- The 3rd European Transport Congress started Thursday (22 April) in the Adriatic town of Opatija.
About 150 experts are participating in the event, representing Southeast European countries, the European Commission, the European Platform for Transport Sciences, and scientific associations from about 20 countries.
The event will focus on transportation links running north to south, as well as within the EU and among its neighbours following the enlargement in May.
(HINA - 22/04//04)
